OL,3,CMore than 1,000 victims protected
OL,4,Cunder domestic abuse order pilot scheme
OL,6,FPerpetrators who breach a DAPO could
OL,7,Fbe subjected to tagging or behaviour
OL,8,Fchange programmes under the stronger,
OL,9,Fmore flexible measures or face up to
OL,10,Ffive years in prison, the Home Office
OL,11,Fand Ministry of Justice said.
OL,13,FMet Police public protection lead,
OL,14,FCommander Clair Kelland, said:
OL,15,F"Although still in the early stages,
OL,16,Fthe pilot scheme is proving these new
OL,17,Fpowers are essential in preventing
OL,18,Fabuse from escalating and ensuring
OL,19,Foffenders face swift action.
